---
title: "Worcester City Council 2025 Election Guide"
---
{% render "header-home.liquid", site: site %}
<main>
  <section>
    <h2>Who's Running for Worcester City Council At-Large?</h2>
    <div class="grid grid--4">
      {% assign candidatesByName = collections.atlarge | sort: "data.sortOrder" %}
      {%- for candidate in candidatesByName -%}
        <div class="card">
          {% render "candidate/summary.liquid", site: site, candidate: candidate, tag: "h3" %}
        </div>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
    <div role="img" aria-label="Wavy Line Shape" class="wavy-line"></div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Who's Running for Worcester District Council?</h2>
    {% assign d1 = collections.d1 | sort: "data.sortOrder" %}
    {% render "district-race.liquid", candidates: d1, district: "District 1", site: site  %}

    {% assign d2 = collections.d2 | sort: "data.sortOrder" %}
    {% render "district-race.liquid", candidates: d2, district: "District 2", site: site %}

    {% assign d3 = collections.d3 | sort: "data.sortOrder" %}
    {% render "district-race.liquid", candidates: d3, district: "District 3", site: site %}

    {% assign d4 = collections.d4 | sort: "data.sortOrder" %}
    {% render "district-race.liquid", candidates: d4, district: "District 4", site: site%}

    {% assign d5 = collections.d5 | sort: "data.sortOrder" %}
    {% render "district-race.liquid", candidates: d5, district: "District 5", site: site %}

    <div role="img" aria-label="Wavy Line Shape" class="wavy-line"></div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Which candidate has raised the most money in 2025?</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="collapsible">
          <div class="collapsible__container collapsible__container--collapsed">
            <table>
              <caption class="table__title">Total donations by candidate</caption>
              <tr>
                <th>Candidate</th>
                <th>$ Raised</th>
                <th>District</th>
              </tr>
              {% assign candidatesByTotal = candidates | sort: "totalDonations" | reverse %}
              {%- for c in candidatesByTotal %}
                {% assign candidate = collections.candidates | find: "data.name", c.name %}
                <tr>
                  <td class="table__candidate">{{c.name}}</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.totalDonations | money}}</td>
                  <td class="table__district">{{candidate.data.tags | district }}</td>
                </tr>
              {%- endfor %}
            </table>
          </div>
          <a class="collapsible__trigger">Show More</a>
        </div>
        <div class="center container container--sm">
          {% render "winner.liquid", name: "Joe Petty" slug: "petty" %}
          <p>Mayor Joe Petty has recently overtaken Satya Mitra for the most donations overall. Petty collected over $11,000 in October, despite almost no campaign spending since September. Most of Petty's donors come from affiliates and members of the Worcester Regional Chamber of Commerce.</p>

          <div class="bottom-link"><a href="{{site.url}}/candidates/satya-mitra">Learn more about Satra Mitra &gt;</a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div role="img" aria-label="Wavy Line Shape" class="wavy-line"></div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Which candidate's donors have the deepest pockets?</h2>
     <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="collapsible">
          <div class="collapsible__container collapsible__container--collapsed">
            <table>
              <caption class="table__title">Average Donation Amount</caption>
              <tr>
                <th>Candidate</th>
                <th>Avg. Donation</th>
                <th># of Donors</th>
              </tr>
              {% assign candidatesByAvg = candidates | sort: "averageDonation" | reverse  %}
              {%- for c in candidatesByAvg %}
                {% assign candidate = collections.candidates | find: "data.name", c.name %}
                <tr>
                  <td class="table__candidate">{{c.name}}</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.averageDonation | money}}</td>
                  <td class="table__district">{{c.donations}}</td>
                </tr>
              {%- endfor %}
            </table>
          </div>
          <a class="collapsible__trigger">Show More</a>
        </div>
        <div class="center container container--sm">
          {% render "winner.liquid", name: "Satya Mitra" slug: "mitra" %}
          <p>Satya Mitra's 232 donors have given an average of $385 each, 50% more than the average of the next candidate (Joe Petty). Mitra has the highest number of donors who have maxed out to the donation limit of $1,000.</p>

          <div class="bottom-link"><a href="{{site.url}}/candidates/joe-petty">Learn more about Joe Petty &gt;</a></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div role="img" aria-label="Wavy Line Shape" class="wavy-line"></div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Where do the candidates donors come from?</h2>
     <div class="grid grid--3">
      <div>
        <h3>Townie's Choice</h3>
        <div class="center">
          {% render "winner.liquid", name: "Gary Rosen" slug: "rosen" %}
        </div>
        <div class="collapsible">
          <div class="collapsible__container collapsible__container--collapsed">
            <table>
              <caption class="table__title">Percentage of donations from Worcester</caption>
              <tr>
                <th>Candidate</th>
                <th>%</th>
                <th>Total</th>
              </tr>
              {% assign candidatesByWorc = candidates | sort: "worcPct" | reverse %}
              {%- for c in candidatesByWorc %}
                {% assign candidate = collections.candidates | find: "data.name", c.name %}
                <tr>
                  <td class="table__candidate">{{c.name}}</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.worcPct | percent}}%</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.worcDonations | money}}</td>
                </tr>
              {%- endfor %}
            </table>
          </div>
          <a class="collapsible__trigger">Show More</a>
          <p>Gary Rosen has the highest percentage of donations from within Worcester at 85%, or $3,668 out of $4,338 total. Despite his lack of campaign funds, Rosen put up a strong performance in the preliminary election. Of those who have raised over $10,000, runner up and incumbent Donna Colorio is the townie queen.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Suburban Influence</h3>
        <div class="center">
          {% render "winner.liquid", name: "Jessica Pepple" slug: "pepple" %}
        </div>
        <div class="collapsible">
          <div class="collapsible__container collapsible__container--collapsed">
            <table>
              <caption class="table__title">Percentage of donations from MA (excluding Worcester)</caption>
              <tr>
                <th>Candidate</th>
                <th>%</th>
                <th>Total</th>
              </tr>
              {% assign candidatesByMA = candidates | sort: "maPct" | reverse %}
              {%- for c in candidatesByMA %}
                {% assign candidate = collections.candidates | find: "data.name", c.name %}
                <tr>
                  <td class="table__candidate">{{c.name}}</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.maPct | percent}}%</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.maDonations | money}}</td>
                </tr>
              {%- endfor %}
            </table>
          </div>
          <a class="collapsible__trigger">Show More</a>
          <p>Jessica Pepple is the suburban peopleâ€™s princess, raising almost all of her money (80.5%) from co-workers at the <a href="https://www.rfkcommunity.org/" target="_blank">RFK Community Alliance</a>. Pepple's total donations are dwarfed by Satya Mitra's, who has raised $58,624 from surrounding areas in Massachusetts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Foreign Agents</h3>
        <div class="center">
          {% render "winner.liquid", name: "Satya Mitra" slug: "mitra" %}
        </div>
        <div class="collapsible">
          <div class="collapsible__container collapsible__container--collapsed">
            <table>
              <caption class="table__title">Percentage of donations from Out-of-State</caption>
              <tr>
                <th>Candidate</th>
                <th>%</th>
                <th>Total</th>
              </tr>
              {% assign candidatesByOos = candidates | sort: "oosPct" | reverse %}
              {%- for c in candidatesByOos %}
                {% assign candidate = collections.candidates | find: "data.name", c.name %}
                <tr>
                  <td class="table__candidate">{{c.name}}</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.oosPct | percent}}%</td>
                  <td class="table__value">{{c.oosDonations | money}}</td>
                </tr>
              {%- endfor %}
            </table>
          </div>
          <a class="collapsible__trigger">Show More</a>
          <p>Luis Ojeda has the largest percentage of funds from out-of-state, due to low total fundraising ($5,531) and a single $1,000 check from a family member. We're giving the out-of-state influence award to Satya Mitra, who has raised the most money ($13,650) from out-of-state interests, 14.3% of his total funds raised.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div role="img" aria-label="Wavy Line Shape" class="wavy-line"></div>
  </section>
</main>
